@startuml
title Séquence – Lecture audio (Text-to-Speech) d'une page
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Utilisateur" as U
boundary "React SPA\n(StoryReader)" as FE
control "API Symfony\nTtsController" as C
control "TtsService" as TtsSvc
entity "PageRepository" as PageRepo
database "MySQL" as DB
participant "API externe\nText-to-Speech" as TTS

U -> FE : Clique "Écouter"
FE -> C : POST /api/tts\n{ pageId, voice, speed }
C -> TtsSvc : synthesizePage(pageId, options)
TtsSvc -> PageRepo : find(pageId)
PageRepo -> DB : SELECT page.content
DB --> PageRepo : page
TtsSvc -> TTS : synthesize(text=page.content,\noptions)
TTS --> TtsSvc : audio (stream/base64/url temporaire)
TtsSvc --> C : audioPayload
C --> FE : 200 JSON { audioPayload }
FE -> FE : Joue l'audio (HTMLAudio)
FE --> U : Son diffusé

note right of TtsSvc
Pas de stockage audio en base :
génération à la demande.
Possibilité de cache court
(mémoire / CDN) en option.
end note

@enduml

